The paper discusses techniques for improving the effectiveness of keyword-based searches in the patent examination process, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of word embedding models, which falls under the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of crowdsourcing, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
